Cell["\<\
Sus[0] is clearly greater than b/a (shown by the red function above the green \
function at t = 0. This corroborates part 3 and part 2 because an epidemic \
occurs and hence the number of susceptible people continually decreases. \
Graphically, the plot range was set up to 10000, meaning that if the function \
ever increased, it would go out of the window (given Sus[0] = 10000).\
\>", "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.7585900035838423`*^9, 3.7585900537483654`*^9}, {
  3.758590353294874*^9, 3.758590396062281*^9}, {3.758590451635664*^9, 
  3.7585906351300497`*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"1f647905-385d-459a-b71e-\
ba839016fb98"]
}, Open  ]]
